-- Amplats to Submit Zimbabwe Black Ownership Plan, Herald Says
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-03-30T10:23:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-30/amplats-to-submit-zimbabwe-black-ownership-plan-herald-says.html
Anglo American Platinum Ltd. (AMS)  will
this week submit plans to  Zimbabwe ’s government outlining how it
will cede control of the Unki mine to black citizens, the state-
controlled Herald said, citing Indigenization Minister  Saviour Kasukuwere .  Under the country’s law, foreign-owned miners must sell or
cede 51 percent of their shares to black Zimbabweans or a
government-owned fund.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  